{"name": "Mighty Physique", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/control/buff-strength-muscle-damage-red.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Your carrying capacity is doubled, and you can attempt to use the Shove, Grapple, or Trip action against a target that is two sizes larger than you at disadvantage.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "WZKVGY28MAZHGYMK", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Toughness", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/defensive/armor-shield-barrier-steel.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Your hit point maximum increases by 1 per level.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "WNJ59P887AGGA1ZA", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Trailblazer", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/tools/navigation/map-plain-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You always know which way is north, and you can accurately retrace your steps along any path you have traveled within the past 7 days.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "activation": {"type": "", "cost": null, "condition": ""}, "duration": {"value": "", "units": ""}, "cover": null, "target": {"value": null, "width": null, "units": "", "type": ""}, "range": {"value": null, "long": null, "units": ""}, "uses": {"value": null, "max": "", "per": null, "recovery": ""}, "consume": {"type": "", "target": null, "amount": null}, "attribute": null, "actionType": "", "attackBonus": "", "chatFlavor": "", "critical": {"threshold": null, "damage": ""}, "damage": {"parts": [], "versatile": ""}, "formula": "", "save": {"attribute": "", "dc": null, "scaling": "spell"}, "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "core"}, "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "HL7IFX1LMPKKB7LJ", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Wild Spirit", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/creatures/abilities/paw-glowing-yellow.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You learn the spell @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-level-1.TT94JMKOUYP2WM96]{Cojoin Familiar} and can cast it once per long rest without expending mana or material components.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "7U9PFUNYXKJE4423", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Fruitful Faith", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/consumables/fruit/apple-red-tree-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>As an action, you can spend 1 @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die to conjure a blessed fruit. Any creature that is holding one of these fruits can use its minor action to eat the fruit, regaining hit points equal to 2d4 + your Wisdom modifier. If you can see a creature when it eats a fruit created by this ability, you can use your reaction to spend any number of @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Dice and add them to the number rolled. When you finish a long rest, any fruits you created that have not been eaten decay. They lose their magic and you regain a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die for each.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Natural Dominion", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "P97169W6CB1L94C4", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Mantras of Nature", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/environment/wilderness/tree-spruce-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>When you learn this ability, the following Mantras are added to your list of available Mantras to choose from.&nbsp; However, these Mantras can only be associated with your <strong>Number of Nature</strong>.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>In addition, when this is unlocked, you can swap out 1 Mantra you know for another one.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><ul><li><strong>Paths Less Traveled:</strong> You gain an additional 10 feet of movement on either your current or next turn.</li><li><strong>The Land Heals in Time:</strong> You regain 1 hit point.</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "J2MKC08RE8DP87NT", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Nature Provides", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/environment/wilderness/tree-spruce-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You gain proficiency with either the Botany, Fishing, or Pathfinding Trade.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "7YFK8JVWZMT9FTKS", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Number of Nature", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/environment/wilderness/tree-spruce-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Your Eikonic Number for the Natural Dominion, known as your Number of Nature, is 8.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "OLMJ9SE59L1T4G3G", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Mantra: Sower of Seasons", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/nature/plant-sproud-hands-dirt-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><em>Unlock:</em> When you have the ability Mantras you may take the ability below</p><p>When you learn this ability, the following Mantras are added to your list of available Mantras to learn, and you can swap up to two of the Mantras you currently know.</p><p>When you learn these Mantras, you may assign them to <strong>any</strong> of your Eikonic numbers. If you have multiple Eikonic Numbers, you can choose to learn each of these Mantras again in order to assign it to another Eikonic Number it is not already assigned to.</p><p>Additionally, wherever you finish a long rest, you can pick one Mantra from this list that is not already assigned to your <strong>Nature Number</strong> and assign it for free. This assignment lasts until your next long rest.</p><ul><li><strong>Spring&rsquo;s Sprawl:</strong> Thorny bushes with flowers or berries appear in a 10ft by 10ft square centered on a point you can see within 30ft of you. Any creature that enters a space with a thorn bush takes 1d4 piercing damage. Flowers produced by the bushes are fragrant, and the berries are sweet but not nutritious or filling. Thorns in a space are destroyed automatically when attacked or if the space is subjected to any fire damage.</li><li><strong>Summer&rsquo;s Glow:</strong> A swarm of fireflies appear in a space you can see (ignoring any obscuration provided by darkness) within 30ft of you and shed dim light in a 5ft radius. The fireflies scatter after 1 minute.</li><li><strong>Autumn&rsquo;s Canvas:</strong> A 5ft tall juvenile tree adorned with autumn leaves emerges in an unoccupied space you can see within 30ft of you. Creatures can move through the tree&rsquo;s space normally. The tree is too weak to support anything larger than a Tiny creature attempting to climb it, but it can provide Half Cover to Medium or smaller creatures obscured by it. At the end of your next turn, all of the leaves fall from the tree and it is no longer suitable for use as cover.</li><li><strong>Winter&rsquo;s Blanket: </strong>A 15ft by 15ft square within 30ft of you is blanketed with snow and becomes difficult terrain. The snow melts at the end of your next turn or when its space is subjected to any fire damage.</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Natural Dominion", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "ES1J6R9RFQJ33HVU", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Natural Dominion Spells", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/environment/wilderness/tree-spruce-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Clerics of the Natural Dominion learn the following spells when able to cast Cleric spells of the same spell level.&nbsp; These spells are always prepared and don&rsquo;t count against your prepared spell amount.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>Dominion spells are considered Cleric spells when learned this way.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><em>Natural Dominion Spells</em></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Able to Cast</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Spells</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1st Level Cleric Spells</p></td><td><p>@Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-1.N4PE33ACTOXHF3FJ]{Biting Wind}, @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-level-1.UP6CZCZNLFNH0ACB]{Song of Adventure}</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2nd Level Cleric Spells</p></td><td><p>Ophidian Kiss*, @Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-2.UEGGABQ79I8A8CG5]{Twister}</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>3rd Level Cleric Spells</p></td><td><p>Astringent Bog, @Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-3.W7NSYVVHKA2Q2MBJ]{Geyser}</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>4th Level Cleric Spells</p></td><td><p>@Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-4.YL8USCAX1ZTDKOA1]{Shapeshift}, @Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-4.2C1AA6FEY5D1JHV5]{Trapdoor Sinkhole}</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>5th Level Cleric Spells</p></td><td><p>Safe Arbor*, @Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-5.H2RO4K8JLYTVNEXB]{Winter's Piercing Ray}</p></td></tr></tbody></table>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "5APSGJ7C1CI9DA0F", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Miracle: Spirit Animal", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/creatures/mammals/spirit-deer-herd-blue.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>When you learn this ability, the following Miracle is added to your list of options available when a Miracle is triggered.<ul><li><b>Custodia Naturalis:</b> You summon a Spirit Animal in an unoccupied space within 15 feet of you, choosing its form to be a Bear, Eagle, Panther, or Wolf. The statistics for the creature are detailed later in this ability. The Spirit Animal acts immediately after your turns in combat and follows your commands. It lasts until you complete a long rest or it drops to 0 hit points. If you activate this miracle while you already have a Spirit Animal summoned, you can replace its form with another from the list, restore all of its hit points, and make it reappear in an unoccupied space within 15 feet of you.</li></ul></p><br><br><h3>Spirit Animal</h3><p>Medium Celestial (Small Celestial in Eagle Form)</p><p>AC 14</p><p>Hit Points 5 + 5 times your Cleric Level</p><p>Speed 40ft, climb 30ft</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>STR</p></td><td><p>DEX</p></td><td><p>CON</p></td><td><p>INT</p></td><td><p>WIS</p></td><td><p>PRE</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>16 (+3)</p></td><td><p>16 (+3)</p></td><td><p>16 (+3)</p></td><td><p>3 (-4)</p></td><td><p>14 (+2)</p></td><td><p>7 (-2)</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Skills: Instinct +4, Perception +4, Stealth + 5</p><p>Awareness: 14</p><p>Challenge: &ndash;-</p><p><strong>Eagle Form.</strong> In Eagle Form, the Spirit Animal loses its climbing speed and half of its move speed, and gains a flying speed of 60 ft.</p><p><strong>Bear Form.</strong> In Bear Form, the Spirit Animal has resistance to bludgeoning, slashing, and piercing damage.</p><p><strong>Wolf Form.</strong> In Wolf Form, the Spirit Animal has advantage on attacks if one or more of its allies are within 5 feet of the target.</p><p><strong>Panther Form.</strong> In Panther Form, the Spirit Animal can hide as a minor action.</p><p><strong>Actions</strong></p><p><strong>Claws.</strong> Melee Weapon Attack: +5 to hit, reach 5 ft, one target. Hit: Deal 1d4+3 slashing damage.</p><p><strong>Bite.</strong> Melee Weapon Attack: +5 to hit, reach 5 ft, one target. Hit: Deal 1d8+3 piercing damage.</p><p><strong>Multiattack. </strong>The Spirit Animal makes one attack with its Bite and one with its Claws.</p><p><strong>Pounce (Panther Form only).</strong> The Spirit Animal makes one attack with its bite. If it was hidden from its target, the attack deals an additional 2d8 damage on a hit.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Natural Dominion", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "1YD5VVREY3QRIR5L", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Squeak Easy", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/creatures/mammals/rabbit-movement-glowing-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You can conduct a 1 minute long ritual to attune yourself to the local wildlife of an area, granting you the ability to converse with the nearby fauna. At the end of the ritual, one or more nearby Beasts (any area with vegetation will usually have at least one Tiny Beast such as a mouse, squirrel, or bird) approaches you and you may ask it questions about the local area. Any beasts you speak to as part of the ritual are considered @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.KJXJ0T5RPNC51N4V]{Charmed} by you for the duration. The creatures have a basic understanding of all of the following within a 1 mile radius: persistent hazards, dangerous monsters, routine humanoid activity, and unusual events that have occurred within the last 10 days. The creatures are not able to identify specific people, kinds of monsters, or iconography but they can provide simple, surface-level descriptions such as \"a huge flying lizard\" for a dragon or \"a big hairy person with horns and a red cloak\" for a minotaur cultist.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The ritual's effects last until you decide to end them, you move more than 30 feet from the spot where you began it, or 1 hour has passed. If one or more of the beasts affected by the ritual are harmed by you or your allies, the effects immediately end and you lose 1 @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Natural Dominion", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "J1I3ZN58X2VSQ2YJ", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Wisdom of the Wilderness", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/environment/wilderness/tree-spruce-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You gain proficiency in Intelligence (Nature) if you were not already proficient in it.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "JWVFZMLVKQEYJGVO", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Blood-Soaked Hands", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/toxins/poison-bottle-open-blood-red.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Your words and actions can stir the cruelest ambitions lurking in the hearts of your fellow incorrigibles. Whenever you <b>Commit to the Bit</b>, any creatures hit by the assisted creature's weapon attacks before the end of its next turn gains the @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.R54LQEKSDXNQ3N75]{Bleeding} condition.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Bard Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "X7GBQG8CSADQYOZH", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Commiseration", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/defensive/illusion-evasion-echo-purple.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You are obsessed with the schemes and passions which rule the mind of man. You gain proficiency in Wisdom (Insight).</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "given"}, "requirements": "Have the Bard Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "M7ONN7XQ5CD8VK24", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Star-Crossed Duel", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/melee/weapons-crossed-swords-pink.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You can sense when it's time for a duel to take a fatal turn. Whenever a @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.conditions.WHN3T2G6R8HUKOQX]{&#x1F9FF; Villainized} creature you can see within 60ft of you is hit with a weapon attack by a @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.conditions.ZOBZ8V2YME5YOYZR]{&#x1F981; Lionized} creature, you can use your reaction to spend 1 @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.ZVH8L715PTWTQLSE]{&#x2728; Flair} point and cause the creature to suffer additional damage equal to your Presence modifier plus two rolls of the @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.conditions.WHN3T2G6R8HUKOQX]{&#x1F9FF; Villainized} bonus die.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;If you activate this ability as a desperate action, it only requires the attacker to be @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.conditions.ZOBZ8V2YME5YOYZR]{&#x1F981; Lionized} or the target to be @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.conditions.WHN3T2G6R8HUKOQX]{&#x1F9FF; Villainized}, not both, and the bonus damage increases by an additional die.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Bard Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "PDP9D8MMKDY2DZSL", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "The Bell Tolls", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/tools/instruments/bell-brass-brown.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>The ghastly visage of death is but a grim reminder of the fallibility of our mortal flesh. As a reaction to the death of a creature you can see, you can single out another creature within 20ft of it to instill terror into. If the target can hear you, it must succeed on a Wisdom (Save) check versus your spell save DC or become @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.UK95BQ45TGSD5Q3V]{Frightened} by the sight of the corpse until the end of its next turn. Succeed or fail, the target can't be affected by this ability again until 24 hours have passed.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Bard Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "AI1FILJPEB8JVZ6L", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Theme: Mortality", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/death/gallows-hanged-humanoid.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Your art is fueled by the pathos that comes with seeing even the mightiest champions brought low by doubt and ill fate. Whenever a creature you can see within 60ft of you is hit by a natural 20 on an attack roll, rolls a natural 1 on a save check, or when one of your allies fails a death throw, gain 1 @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.ZVH8L715PTWTQLSE]{&#x2728; Flair} point.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;You can only benefit from one Theme ability at a time. If you have multiple Theme abilities, you can change which one is active when you finish a short or long rest and any time you spend a @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.ZVH8L715PTWTQLSE]{&#x2728; Flair} point on an ability.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "given"}, "requirements": "Have the Bard Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "4A26NHYUBD8OXCX5", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Untimely Remorse", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/death/grave-tombstone-glow-teal.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>As a reaction to one of your allies being reduced to 0 hit points or killed, you can force the creature responsible to make a Wisdom (Save) Check versus your spell save DC. On a failure, the creature is overcome with grief, surprise, or some other unexpected emotion, and is @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.3CQC3JEY2C3Y721F]{Incapacitated} until the start of its next turn.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;If your ally was killed instantly, the creature has disadvantage on the save.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Bard Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "9KHMDNUC50478I0D", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
